:R-HSA-399719  a            obo:GO_0008150 , owl:NamedIndividual ;
        rdfs:comment        "Repetitive presynaptic activity causes long lasting changes in the postsynaptic transmission by changing the type and the number of AMPA receptors. These changes are brought about by trafficking mechanisms that are mainly controlled by activity dependent phosphorylation/desphosphorylation of the GluR1/GluR2 subunits." ;
        rdfs:label          "Trafficking of AMPA receptors" ;
